Overview
The Strange Math Creature Zoo is a mnemonic classification system 
that organizes mathematical concepts into themed “wings” populated 
by metaphorical creatures. It functions as a knowledge‑organization 
scaffold, not a mathematical research paper. Its role in the domain‑
papers repository is to provide cross‑domain indexing, memory aids, 
and conceptual mapping structures.

